darling.

45
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,180
Yeah.

46
00:03:09,470 --> 00:03:11,400
I dunno...

47
00:03:12,910 --> 00:03:15,600
I never found out what happened that day,

48
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:18,080
and Akari went back to normal, like nothing had happened.

49
00:03:19,850 --> 00:03:24,020
But she cried so much, and she still seems determined to switch partners.

50
00:03:24,020 --> 00:03:26,100
Is that how much she wants to be with Tenjin?

51
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:28,930
Jiro!

52
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:31,110
This is terrible!

53
00:03:32,910 --> 00:03:34,880
What is it? What happened?

54
00:03:37,690 --> 00:03:40,240
That creep showed up! Help me!

55
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,530
Huh? What creep?

56
00:03:41,530 --> 00:03:45,040
Please! Please! Please! Hurry! Hurry, Jiro!

57
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:48,080
Calm down, Akari! Who showed up?

58
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:49,700
A spider!

59
00:03:52,380 --> 00:03:54,570
Don't barge in on me in the bath over a stupid spider!

60
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:55,740
I'm stark naked here!

61
00:03:55,740 --> 00:03:57,470
What do you mean, "a stupid spider"?

62
00:03:57,470 --> 00:03:59,050
And who cares about a body like yours?!

63
00:03:59,050 --> 00:04:00,710
Whoa! That counterattack hit hard!

64
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:02,910
I don't care!

65
00:04:02,910 --> 00:04:05,490
Just do something about that creep right now!

66
00:04:05,490 --> 00:04:07,390
I can't go back into the living room!

67
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:08,580
Wait, wait, wait, wait!

68
00:04:08,580 --> 00:04:10,700
Get me my towel and clothes first!

69
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:14,060
So?

70
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:16,440
Where is this spider?

71
00:04:20,670 --> 00:04:23,070
It... It's gone!

72
00:04:23,390 --> 00:04:25,570
Stay calm. How big was it?

73
00:04:25,870 --> 00:04:27,300
About this big.

74
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:28,580
Huh? That's tiny!

75
00:04:28,580 --> 00:04:31,480
It doesn't matter how small it is! I can't handle spiders!

76
00:04:32,830 --> 00:04:34,860
All right, I get it. Sorry.

77
00:04:34,860 --> 00:04:36,350
I'm dealing with hugeness myself.

78
00:04:36,350 --> 00:04:39,820
It might suddenly show up again.

79
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:42,570
She's cute when she's meek and quiet.

80
00:04:42,570 --> 00:04:44,160
Hey, I want a snack.

81
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:45,430
Go ahead.

82
00:04:45,430 --> 00:04:47,360
Come to the kitchen with me!

83
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:48,050
Huh?

84
00:04:48,050 --> 00:04:49,760
Okay. Forward!

85
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,930
But that's only when she's being meek and quiet.

86
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:55,800
I ate too much.

87
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,560
Gotta do my nails next.

88
00:04:57,900 --> 00:05:00,060
How long should I stay here?

89
00:05:00,060 --> 00:05:04,060
Well... until the spider shows up and you catch it.

90
00:05:04,060 --> 00:05:07,090
Oh, come on. If you call for me, I'll come right back.

91
00:05:07,090 --> 00:05:08,820
Then I'm calling for you now.

92
00:05:09,830 --> 00:05:11,820
It'll be scary if it suddenly shows up again.

93
00:05:11,820 --> 00:05:15,370
The feel of that hugeness against my leg!

94
00:05:20,860 --> 00:05:22,000
Jiro...

95
00:05:24,860 --> 00:05:25,920
Come with me?

96
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,390
Are you serious?!

97
00:05:29,030 --> 00:05:31,850
Jiro! You're there, right?

98
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:33,860
Yes.

99
00:05:34,350 --> 00:05:36,500
Cover your ears, okay?

100
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:38,090
Right! The sound!

101
00:05:38,090 --> 00:05:38,800
Jiro? I said I'm here!

102
00:05:39,780 --> 00:05:41,020
You can still hear!

103
00:05:41,020 --> 00:05:42,980
I was just about to cover my ears!

104
00:05:42,980 --> 00:05:44,000
It's no good.

105
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,950
I can't help but imagine what's happening in there, even if I don't want to!

106
00:05:46,950 --> 00:05:48,440
Please, hurry up and come out!

107
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:51,020
While my conscience still lives!

108
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:55,120
Sorry to keep you waiting.

109
00:05:57,090 --> 00:05:59,980
I'll go, too. Saves me having to come back.

110
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,880
I know! It'll just take a few seconds!

111
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:10,260
I wish I could die!

112
00:06:10,650 --> 00:06:12,500
This is the worst! The absolute worst!

113
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,940
Asking him to come to the bathroom with me is so wrong!

114
00:06:14,940 --> 00:06:17,270
I'm so embarrassed, I just want to disappear.

115
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:22,260
But since it's Jiro, I figured he'd come with me instead of saying no.

116
00:06:22,890 --> 00:06:25,670
I'm glad Jiro's the one with me.

117
00:06:25,670 --> 00:06:28,400
I'd never be able to ask Minami-kun for something like this.

118
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:32,280
Here.

119
00:06:34,230 --> 00:06:35,290
Let's head back.

120
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:37,630
You washed your hands?

121
00:06:37,630 --> 00:06:39,040
Freshly washed!

122
00:06:42,910 --> 00:06:44,420
Thanks.

123
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:49,930
And after the way she was just minutes ago...

124
00:06:50,650 --> 00:06:53,650
I really am living with a gyaru.

125
00:06:53,650 --> 00:06:57,090
At first, I thought it'd never work, but somehow or other...

126
00:06:57,090 --> 00:06:58,930
Hey, I want some of that, too.

127
00:06:59,340 --> 00:07:01,290
Oh, there's some in the freezer.

128
00:07:01,290 --> 00:07:01,940
What?

129
00:07:01,940 --> 00:07:03,590
I can't go. I'm scared of the spider.

130
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:05,670
I just want one bite, so yours is fine.

131
00:07:05,670 --> 00:07:07,130
Then I'll get a spoon and—

132
00:07:07,130 --> 00:07:07,940
Nope!

133
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,950
I can't use my hands.

134
00:07:10,470 --> 00:07:13,760
Oh, you're thinking about indirect kisses now, aren't you?

135
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:15,330
You're such a little kid!

136
00:07:15,330 --> 00:07:17,450
Why would you bring that up right now?

137
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:19,460
Come on, hurry up.

138
00:07:19,850 --> 00:07:22,460
It's yours I want, Jiro. Give it to me.

139
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:26,960
O spirits, calm thyselves! Jewels! Jewels! Family jewels!

140
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:28,960
Here.

141
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,970
What?

142
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:42,240
You used to like chocolate ice cream.

143
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:44,730
Do you think we're getting to be more alike?

144
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:48,400
Hey, did something good happen to you today?

145
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:51,840
Huh? Nothing in particular. You're funny.

146
00:07:55,830 --> 00:07:57,550
Hey, hypothetically speaking...

147
00:07:57,550 --> 00:08:01,870
If you and I had met somewhere else, what do you think would've happened?

148
00:08:02,350 --> 00:08:05,470
We never would have talked, probably.

149
00:08:05,470 --> 00:08:07,090
What? You're so mean.

150
00:08:07,090 --> 00:08:11,440
I think I might've wanted to meet a Jiro who wasn't my husband.

151
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:12,380
Huh?

152
00:08:12,380 --> 00:08:15,660
You'd be hilarious, with all your gloom-and-doom on display.

153
00:08:15,660 --> 00:08:18,640
But we don't have anything in common, so we wouldn't have hit it off.

154
00:08:19,020 --> 00:08:21,390
The other pairs are probably like that, too.

155
00:08:21,390 --> 00:08:23,230
But the fifth-place pair are dating, right?

156
00:08:23,230 --> 00:08:26,020
Well, they're sort of an exception.

157
00:08:26,650 --> 00:08:28,420
Should we try dating, too?

158
00:08:35,820 --> 00:08:37,710
Just kidding!

159
00:08:37,710 --> 00:08:40,910
Look! I think my nails turned out really nice today!

160
00:08:41,430 --> 00:08:43,050
Do you mind if I turn on the TV?

161
00:08:43,050 --> 00:08:43,910
G-Go ahead.

162
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:48,170
Why did I think about it for a second?

163
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:51,120
There's no way she was serious about it!

164
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:53,830
If she were serious, she wouldn't say it so casually.

165
00:08:54,380 --> 00:08:55,710
If she were serious...

166
00:08:56,370 --> 00:08:58,970
what answer would I have given her?

167
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,680
If we weren't a married couple...

168
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:06,140
If we'd met while I had no idea Jiro loved someone else...

169
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:15,150
Spider! Spider! Spider!

170
00:09:15,150 --> 00:09:16,320
Huh?! What?!

171
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:18,320
You mean that? It's tiny!

172
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:20,330
Please! Do something, Jiro!

173
00:09:19,470 --> 00:09:21,330
W-W-Wait! Wait! Wait!

174
00:09:21,330 --> 00:09:22,990
Akari! Let go!

175
00:09:24,330 --> 00:09:25,480
Jiro!

176
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:29,080
Th-This hot sensation on the back of my hand...

177
00:09:29,630 --> 00:09:31,590
A-Akari...

178
00:09:32,330 --> 00:09:36,160
Why are you just sitting there spacing out?! Hurry up and do something!

179
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:39,340
I will! I'll do something! Just please let go of me!

180
00:09:41,780 --> 00:09:42,600
Here.

181
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,600
I'll buy this for next time.

182
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:46,390
No.

183
00:09:46,390 --> 00:09:47,420
What do you mean, "no"?

184
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:50,080
I don't wanna touch it after I've sprayed it.

185
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:54,090
You say that now, but what if your next husband hates bugs?

186
00:09:54,090 --> 00:09:55,680
It won't be a problem.

187
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:58,820
Because if I call for a certain someone, he'll come right away.

188
00:09:58,820 --> 00:09:59,620
Right?

189
00:10:01,230 --> 00:10:04,810
Don't go skipping a beat there, heart. She's just toying with you!

190
00:10:04,810 --> 00:10:07,500
Well, goodnight, darling!

191
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:11,020
Seriously... What am I, your bug exterminator?

192
00:10:12,560 --> 00:10:15,510
In any case, I'll be counting on you for a little while longer,

193
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:16,800
Akari.

194
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,750
Shiori? What's wrong?

195
00:10:52,740 --> 00:10:54,080
Minami-kun.

196
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:55,520
Something on your mind?

197
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:58,360
You can talk to me about it, though I'm not sure if I'll be any help.

198
00:10:59,590 --> 00:11:00,760
Thank you.

199
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:05,280
Remember when I told you about my friend who reunited with a boy she liked?

200
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:06,100
Yeah.

201
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:08,470
It's about that friend again...

202
00:11:08,470 --> 00:11:09,100
Okay.

203
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:10,520
Th...

204
00:11:10,810 --> 00:11:12,270
They kissed.

205
00:11:12,970 --> 00:11:16,520
I-It was an accident! They aren't dating yet.

206
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:20,130
But she doesn't know how to face him anymore.

207
00:11:20,130 --> 00:11:25,430
I don't—I mean, she doesn't know how the boy feels about her,

208
00:11:25,430 --> 00:11:28,220
so she's worried that he didn't like it.

209
00:11:29,580 --> 00:11:30,540
But the thing is...

210
00:11:30,540 --> 00:11:34,540
Worrying about it made her realize that she really does love him.

211
00:11:34,540 --> 00:11:39,050
All she can think about ever since then is that kiss.

212
00:11:39,340 --> 00:11:42,880
But she doesn't know if she wants to tell him how she feels or not.

213
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:43,940
She's scared.

214
00:11:44,420 --> 00:11:45,980
What should she do, Minami-kun?

215
00:11:45,980 --> 00:11:47,290
Minami-kun?!

216
00:11:47,930 --> 00:11:49,400
Y-Your tea!

217
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:51,470
Sorry, I wasn't looking.

218
00:11:51,470 --> 00:11:53,510
It's okay. The sofa didn't get wet.

219
00:11:53,510 --> 00:11:55,190
Here's a towel.

220
00:11:58,350 --> 00:12:01,950
The reason she's scared must be because she's hoping for something, right?

221
00:12:04,650 --> 00:12:05,570
But...

222
00:12:06,330 --> 00:12:09,580
If there's any possibility it'll work out, I think she should try for it.

223
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:13,630
The guy she wants to tell is the one she was able to fall in love with.

224
00:12:13,630 --> 00:12:16,600
It'd be a waste if she ended up being too late, like me.

225
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,740
I'm sorry, I...

226
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:21,590
No, no, I didn't mean it like that.

227
00:12:21,590 --> 00:12:22,620
I don't want you—

228
00:12:23,180 --> 00:12:25,990
I mean, your friend—to have any regrets,

229
00:12:25,990 --> 00:12:28,350
and if I can help with that, I'd like to.

230
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:30,480
Thank you.

231
00:12:31,370 --> 00:12:34,410
I'm glad I got paired with you, Minami-kun.

232
00:12:34,410 --> 00:12:37,610
Oh, I know. What about asking if he hated the kiss?

233
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:39,710
That's just impossible!

234
00:12:39,710 --> 00:12:40,730
For your friend?

235
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:44,170
"I think you should have more confidence."

236
00:12:44,170 --> 00:12:45,980
Tell your friend I said that.

237
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:50,470
Confidence?

238
00:12:53,370 --> 00:12:56,370
I'm telling you, you should be more confident in yourself, Shiori.

239
00:12:56,820 --> 00:12:58,290
This off-the-shoulder look is nice!

240
00:12:58,290 --> 00:13:01,090
Yakuin's a guy, so he'll like this kind of thing.

241
00:13:01,090 --> 00:13:04,580
Come on, Mei-chan! We're picking something out for you right now!

242
00:13:04,580 --> 00:13:07,490
But I just know you'd look cute if you wore it.

243
00:13:07,490 --> 00:13:09,780
I know you would, since you have such nice legs.

244
00:13:09,780 --> 00:13:11,110
What do you think of this?

245
00:13:11,110 --> 00:13:13,630
I've got tan lines from my running shorts.

246
00:13:14,110 --> 00:13:16,650
Then how about this? I think the red would suit you!

247
00:13:16,650 --> 00:13:18,400
Stop thinking about what would suit me.

248
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:21,310
I want you to pick out something you like.

249
00:13:21,310 --> 00:13:23,280
What? But...

250
00:13:24,150 --> 00:13:26,400
After all, you'll be the one who sees it.

251
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,910
I'll be wearing it the next time we go to the movies.

252
00:13:29,330 --> 00:13:32,910
So make me into a me that you like.

253
00:13:35,410 --> 00:13:37,600
I think I know how your fans feel now!

254
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:40,320
Anyone who dates you will be very happy!

255
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:42,170
You say that so easily.

256
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:45,480
There are people I can't make happy, you know.

257
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:49,630
I'm sure those people just don't know how wonderful you are, that's all.

258
00:13:49,630 --> 00:13:51,530
Maybe I'll go tell them.

259
00:13:51,530 --> 00:13:54,880
How 'bout instead, you go hug Yakuin, tell him everything's gonna be okay,

260
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:56,810
and teach him why it's great to be an adult.

261
00:13:56,810 --> 00:13:59,250
Then just throw yourself at him right there!

262
00:13:59,250 --> 00:14:01,720
M-Mei-chan, not so loud!

263
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:03,320
Hamano!

264
00:14:03,990 --> 00:14:05,280
Hey, what's up?

265
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:06,310
Hey.

266
00:14:06,310 --> 00:14:08,900
I have an interview for a part-time job today, so I won't need dinner.

267
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:11,260
Okay. Is it that place you mentioned before?

268
00:14:11,260 --> 00:14:13,580
Yeah. The place by the station, with the star.

269
00:14:13,580 --> 00:14:16,110
Is that the same place as Minami-kun?

270
00:14:16,110 --> 00:14:16,920
That's right.

271
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:20,790
Oh! I've been worried since Minami-kun seemed to be working too hard lately,

272
00:14:20,790 --> 00:14:22,810
but I feel better knowing you'll be with him!

273
00:14:22,810 --> 00:14:25,610
Yeah, this guy is surprisingly considerate.

274
00:14:25,610 --> 00:14:27,920
Ooh, a rare word of praise from my wife.

275
00:14:27,920 --> 00:14:28,590
Hey! Oh, right.

276
00:14:29,580 --> 00:14:33,180
I asked Tenjin to do karaoke with me after dinner, and we'll be going all night.

277
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:37,480
You two wives should eat together and stay over at one of our places.

278
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:38,370
Stay—

279
00:14:38,370 --> 00:14:41,130
Sometimes spending the night together is nice, right?

280
00:14:41,470 --> 00:14:43,290
Just the two of you and a hot night.

281
00:14:43,290 --> 00:14:44,110
Are you seri—

282
00:14:44,110 --> 00:14:45,120
That sounds nice!

283
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:46,610
Let's do it, Mei-chan!

284
00:14:46,610 --> 00:14:47,960
Let's have a sleepover!

285
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:48,670
Huh?

286
00:14:48,670 --> 00:14:50,990
Oh, did you have other plans?

287
00:14:50,990 --> 00:14:52,700
No, but...

288
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:55,670
I'm not "surprisingly" considerate, I'm super considerate, right?

289
00:14:55,670 --> 00:14:57,370
No one asked for your help!

290
00:14:57,370 --> 00:14:59,210
I never should have said anything to you!

291
00:14:59,210 --> 00:15:01,800
So, that's what we're doing. You two get along, okay?

292
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:02,660
I swear...

293
00:15:02,660 --> 00:15:05,770
I can't wait! What should we do for dinner?

294
00:15:05,770 --> 00:15:07,360
Yeah, what should we do?

295
00:15:07,880 --> 00:15:08,920
Sorry! Come do a karaoke all-nighter with me after the meeting today I already got the okay from your wife! Then we might see each other at the shop Thanks in advance

296
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:10,180
Then we might see each other at the shop Thanks in advance Sorry! Come do a karaoke all-nighter with me after the meeting today I already got the okay from your wife! I'll never ask for anything again!!

297
00:15:08,950 --> 00:15:11,640
"I'll never ask for anything again."

298
00:15:10,180 --> 00:15:13,680
Then we might see each other at the shop Thanks in advance Sorry! Come do a karaoke all-nighter with me after the meeting today I already got the okay from your wife! I'll never ask for anything again!!

299
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:17,180
Sorry! Come do a karaoke all-nighter with me after the meeting today I already got the okay from your wife! I'll never ask for anything again!! Roger that

300
00:15:15,140 --> 00:15:16,060
Yes!

301
00:15:17,180 --> 00:15:18,390
I'll never ask for anything again!! Roger that You use the "I'll ever ask for anything again" line too much

302
00:15:18,910 --> 00:15:21,560
This is how a married couple should be!

303
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:23,900
Man! It's so good, it's gonna make me cry!

304
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:28,400
Sugi

305
00:15:24,710 --> 00:15:26,400
Are you listening, Teranishi?

306
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:28,480
Mikkun is...

307
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:29,900
My name is Terafune.

308
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:33,660
He's working hard at my café so he can move out after he graduates!

309
00:15:33,980 --> 00:15:37,410
Why, you ask? Because Mikkun and his older brother...

310
00:15:37,410 --> 00:15:40,160
share a super tragic fate—

311
00:15:40,160 --> 00:15:42,260
You've had too much to drink, Kamo-san.

312
00:15:42,260 --> 00:15:44,670
And I told him all about this last year.

313
00:15:44,670 --> 00:15:45,880
Yeah?

314
00:15:46,470 --> 00:15:49,140
It must be rough having ikemen DNA, right?

315
00:15:49,140 --> 00:15:51,000
Even your siblings are your rivals!

316
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:53,730
Makes us glad we're not ikemen ourselves, right, Terashima?

317
00:15:53,730 --> 00:15:55,040
My name is Terafune.

318
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:56,700
Tenjin, what's your older brother like again?

319
00:15:56,970 --> 00:15:58,170
Do you guys look alike?

320
00:15:58,650 --> 00:15:59,930
He's just average.

321
00:15:59,930 --> 00:16:03,800
An ikemen should never say that! It insults all of us non-ikemen!

322
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:06,420
As punishment, drip-filter your handsomeness and let us drink it!

323
00:16:06,420 --> 00:16:07,420
Right, Terasaka? My name is Terafune.

324
00:16:08,340 --> 00:16:12,450
I sure am glad my little brothers are average, though.

325
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:12,450
Excuse me!

326
00:16:12,450 --> 00:16:13,850
Can we get some water? Wait. Are they less than average?

327
00:16:13,850 --> 00:16:16,070
Of course. Coming right up. Oh, you have little brothers?

328
00:16:16,070 --> 00:16:18,980
You didn't know? That guy with the glasses in our class is one of them.

329
00:16:18,980 --> 00:16:20,500
The one who's friends with Yakuin.

330
00:16:21,620 --> 00:16:23,680
Yakuin...

331
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:25,700
Sure is a small world, huh?

332
00:16:27,090 --> 00:16:30,120
I was so sure it wouldn't work out.

333
00:16:30,120 --> 00:16:32,090
Why are they thirteenth?

334
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:34,930
I met Watanabe first!

335
00:16:34,930 --> 00:16:37,000
What does he have that I don't?

336
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,920
Height and luck! That's about it!

337
00:16:38,920 --> 00:16:40,810
Ugh. Those flaws are pretty fatal...

338
00:16:40,810 --> 00:16:42,550
What?! Stories of unrequited love?!

339
00:16:42,550 --> 00:16:43,890
Those are my favorite!

340
00:16:43,890 --> 00:16:46,350
Come on, Kamo-san. Drink some water.

341
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:49,690
Okay, it's decided!

342
00:16:49,690 --> 00:16:51,710
We'll spend the night at my place.

343
00:16:51,710 --> 00:16:53,240
You can use the bed, Mei-chan.

344
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:56,290
Huh? N-No, I'll be fine sleeping on the floor.

345
00:16:56,290 --> 00:16:57,740
No, I can't make you do that.

346
00:16:57,970 --> 00:17:01,790
Oh! Should we open up the sofa in the living room and sleep together instead?

347
00:17:01,790 --> 00:17:03,000
T-Together?!

348
00:17:03,590 --> 00:17:04,910
No, no, no.

349
00:17:04,910 --> 00:17:06,500
Let's take a bath together, too!

350
00:17:07,770 --> 00:17:09,500
A-Are you all right, Mei-chan?!

351
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:10,000
Sorry.

352
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:12,710
It went down the wrong pipe. I'm fine.

353
00:17:12,710 --> 00:17:17,110
Oh, but I wanted to see the old photos in your room.

354
00:17:17,110 --> 00:17:18,140
You have them up, right?

355
00:17:18,710 --> 00:17:21,810
Like the photo from when we won that tournament in middle school!

356
00:17:21,810 --> 00:17:24,510
I don't have anything like that. All my pictures are of family.

357
00:17:24,510 --> 00:17:25,890
Oh, really?

358
00:17:25,890 --> 00:17:28,710
Do you have any old photos up?

359
00:17:28,710 --> 00:17:29,970
Just a few.

360
00:17:30,450 --> 00:17:32,680
I'm looking forward to seeing little Shiori.

361
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:35,400
Oh, but it might be a little embarrassing.

362
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:39,100
Most of them are of me and Jiro-kun.

363
00:17:40,900 --> 00:17:42,540
Of course.

364
00:17:46,090 --> 00:17:47,570
Oh, sorry.

365
00:17:47,570 --> 00:17:49,550
My mom asked me to do something right away,

366
00:17:49,550 --> 00:17:51,670
so I have to go to my parents' house from here.

367
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:52,770
What?

368
00:17:52,770 --> 00:17:55,920
Sorry! We'll do this another time, okay?

369
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:58,720
Chef's Kiss Marinated Maguro Bowl Chef's Kiss Marinated Maguro Bowl

370
00:17:58,720 --> 00:18:01,840
Why did I end up eating dinner with the same guy I see all the time?

371
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:03,930
You're the one who invited me.

372
00:18:03,930 --> 00:18:07,350
Well, my wife told me out of the blue to go eat out somewhere.

373
00:18:07,350 --> 00:18:10,000
I bet she's complaining about me right now.

374
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,220
But things are going all right, aren't they?

375
00:18:12,220 --> 00:18:16,190
Well, we aren't as cozy as someone sitting in thirteenth place.

376
00:18:16,190 --> 00:18:16,800
Cozy?

377
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,480
What do you mean, "kissed by accident"?

378
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:20,220
This isn't a harem anime.

379
00:18:20,220 --> 00:18:23,360
How can an accident cause lips to lock with lips?

380
00:18:23,360 --> 00:18:24,870
I don't know what to tell you...

381
00:18:25,190 --> 00:18:28,280
Hey, Jiro-chan. It's almost summer, you know.

382
00:18:27,690 --> 00:18:31,030
Stupid Kamo. The way you use your hands is so naughty. I don't want a fake wife. I want a girlfriend!

383
00:18:31,030 --> 00:18:33,760
I want to try falling in love in the 3D world, too!

384
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:35,450
No, I don't need love!

385
00:18:35,450 --> 00:18:37,630
If I can escape virginhood, that's good enough!

386
00:18:37,630 --> 00:18:39,680
If you have to actually say that, you know it's impossible.

387
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:41,760
Shut up, you traitor!

388
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:42,850
We had an alliance.

389
00:18:42,850 --> 00:18:45,500
And you call yourself my childhood friend? Blast you!

390
00:18:44,730 --> 00:18:46,770
Are you drunk or something?!

391
00:18:47,580 --> 00:18:49,770
Hey. What's come over you all of a sudden?

392
00:18:50,020 --> 00:18:53,270
I will cancel out your luck-based lechery.

393
00:18:54,130 --> 00:18:55,020
What?

394
00:19:01,660 --> 00:19:04,880
It's no use. When I'm alone, I can't help but...

395
00:19:06,040 --> 00:19:08,540
Kiss

396
00:19:08,540 --> 00:19:14,540
Chef's Kiss Marinated Maguro Bowl

397
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:19,300
I will use my lips to overwrite the save data.

398
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:21,290
Hey, be serious! You're scaring me!

399
00:19:21,290 --> 00:19:23,890
That won't just overwrite! I'll suffer a physical crash!

400
00:19:22,930 --> 00:19:24,800
It's simply an equivalent exchange.

401
00:19:25,810 --> 00:19:29,110
No!

402
00:19:29,110 --> 00:19:29,560
Huh?

403
00:19:35,570 --> 00:19:39,190
Shiori, it's not like that.

404
00:19:39,190 --> 00:19:39,810
Ow!

405
00:19:39,810 --> 00:19:40,990
Keep the change!

406
00:19:44,710 --> 00:19:46,490
There's something wrong with me.

407
00:19:46,490 --> 00:19:49,870
Imagine reading "Chef's Kiss Marinated Maguro Bowl" as just "Kiss Bowl."

408
00:19:49,870 --> 00:19:50,830
Shiori!

409
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:52,020
Jiro-kun?

410
00:19:52,020 --> 00:19:54,820
You've got it all wrong! It wasn't like that at all!

411
00:19:54,820 --> 00:19:55,340
Huh?

412
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:56,960
Do you mean...

413
00:19:59,010 --> 00:20:01,220
I just don't want you to misunderstand...

414
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:03,790
It was just kind of an accident...

415
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:05,970
Yeah. I know.

416
00:20:05,970 --> 00:20:07,570
I'm the one who should apologize.

417
00:20:07,570 --> 00:20:09,560
It's fine. I'm not bothered by it at all.

418
00:20:09,560 --> 00:20:10,830
Thank goodness!

419
00:20:10,830 --> 00:20:13,730
Kamo was panicking and slipped into some weird mode.

420
00:20:13,730 --> 00:20:16,480
Huh? Why are you mentioning Kamo-kun?

421
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:19,860
Huh? Well, Kamo was the one I was goofing off with at that restaurant.

422
00:20:19,860 --> 00:20:22,360
You were at a restaurant?

423
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:23,170
Huh?

424
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:24,330
Huh?

425
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:25,830
Huh?

426
00:20:27,830 --> 00:20:30,880
I-I'm so sorry! I think I was talking about something else!

427
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:32,640
I'm sorry! I was mistaken, too.

428
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:34,580
Seriously, please forget all of it.

429
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:38,320
Th-That looks heavy.

430
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:40,840
Oh... I ended up buying too much.

431
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:44,000
I'll carry it. Oh, if you don't mind, that is.

432
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,870
What? Y-You don't mind?

433
00:20:46,890 --> 00:20:47,760
Sure.

434
00:20:51,460 --> 00:20:54,890
If Shiori and I were married, this is what it'd be like.

435
00:20:55,570 --> 00:20:59,120
I'm probably the only one thinking that way, though.

436
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:02,270
It's funny, isn't it? When we're like this, it's almost like we're marr—

437
00:21:02,270 --> 00:21:02,980
Huh?

438
00:21:02,980 --> 00:21:04,080
Nothing!

439
00:21:04,080 --> 00:21:05,540
What? Come on, tell me.

440
00:21:05,540 --> 00:21:07,090
It's nothing.

441
00:21:07,670 --> 00:21:10,940
Thank you for carrying this with me, Jiro-kun.

442
00:21:13,750 --> 00:21:15,390
When I was in the nurse's office, too...

443
00:21:15,390 --> 00:21:16,860
I'm sorry about that!

444
00:21:16,860 --> 00:21:19,000
It was all my fault. I'm really sorry.

445
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,380
No, I—P-Please listen, Jiro-kun!

446
00:21:21,610 --> 00:21:23,350
You don't have to apologize.

447
00:21:23,350 --> 00:21:24,270
Huh?

448
00:21:24,270 --> 00:21:25,630
I mean...

449
00:21:26,150 --> 00:21:27,390
Uh...

450
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:31,600
I was the one who asked you to teach me.

451
00:21:33,330 --> 00:21:37,400
And... I-I learned a lot.

452
00:21:38,640 --> 00:21:41,900
That that's what a... k-kiss feels like...

453
00:21:43,150 --> 00:21:45,900
It wasn't that I didn't want you to.

454
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:49,530
So... thank you.

455
00:21:50,750 --> 00:21:52,570
She's saying all this to me,

456
00:21:52,570 --> 00:21:56,040
and she still wants me to just stay her friend forever?

457
00:22:04,550 --> 00:22:06,670
It's even warm at night now, huh?

458
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:08,220
Shall we head home?

459
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:11,680
Let's head home, Jiro-kun!

460
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:14,430
Soon, summer will be here again...

461
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:18,040
The third summer since Shiori came back.

462
00:22:19,940 --> 00:22:23,920
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

463
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:28,350
I want to give love a try

464
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:31,260
In this night when everything begins to overflow

465
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:33,530
I match my stride to yours

466
00:22:33,530 --> 00:22:39,390
The clock hands stop, charmed by a fleeting curse

467
00:22:39,390 --> 00:22:43,940
The answers always slip away

468
00:22:43,940 --> 00:22:47,360
All I want is to do it over again

469
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:52,760
If I did, would this unsettling gloom inside me disappear?

470
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:57,080
I want to know where my heart is hiding

471
00:22:57,080 --> 00:23:01,840
One day this will end

472
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:04,640
I know that

473
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:06,350
And I know the signs of discord

474
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:08,420
Turn them inside out

475
00:23:08,420 --> 00:23:10,000
Don't let them pile up

476
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:14,210
I don't want things to stay unfinished like this

477
00:23:14,210 --> 00:23:18,250
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

478
00:23:18,250 --> 00:23:22,680
I want to give love a try

479
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:24,700
Everything begins to overflow

480
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:27,890
On this day when we don't know how much time is left to us

481
00:23:27,890 --> 00:23:36,150
I want your thoughts to drift toward me fondly, again and again

482
00:23:50,560 --> 00:23:52,800
Sadaharu-kun, kiss me.

483
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:53,990
What is this? A dream?

484
00:23:53,990 --> 00:23:56,810
Your first kiss is with me! Right, Sada?

485
00:23:56,810 --> 00:23:57,990
She called me Sada.

486
00:23:57,990 --> 00:24:00,300
Why are you getting in the way? You're the one getting in the way!

487
00:23:59,170 --> 00:24:01,350
Huh? Wait. You two?

488
00:24:01,350 --> 00:24:02,330
A little further and... Smooch.

489
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:06,500
Why did I wake up there?!

490
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:10,010
Next Time More Than a Childhood Friend, But Not True Love.

491
00:24:06,780 --> 00:24:08,880
Next time, "More Than a Childhood Friend..."

492
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:10,010
"...But Not True Love."

